  "text": "Skip to main contentWhile each product featured is independently selected by our editors, we may include paid promotion. If you buy something through our links, we may earn commission. Read more about our Product Review Guidelines here.The Y2K era has dominated the sartorial food chain in recent years, from baguette bags and charmcore to crop tops and flared jeans. While we've enjoyed adding these items in abundance to our wardrobes, there's a new girl on the block who deserves our coins even more: the jort. Otherwise known as jean shorts that hit just above the knee or lower, the bottom has found its way to the top of our FYPs (once again), after taking over last summer. To no surprise, style stars and designers alike have cosigned jorts as the official it-piece to have in your wardrobe, from SZA and Hailey Bieber to the runways of Etro and Fiorucci during Milan Fashion Week's Spring 2025 season. And as with many other trends, the denim style dates back to the early aughts, with stars like Beyoncé having donned skinny jean jorts on many occasion and Madonna's casual looks often defined by long, oversized menswear jorts. All this to say, jorts are so back, and this is your sign to give into the fad. Far from a thing of the past, the comfortable bottom has evolved into many iterations, from playful prints to deconstructed waistlines — so there's truly something for everyone. Looking for a functional frayed pair for your summer escapades? Nordstrom's offerings fit the bill. And if you're on the hunt for a pair that can go from the office to date night with that special someone, we found the perfect pair from ASOS. Ahead, we've gathered the best jorts for every aesthetic and shape, from affordable finds to splurge-worthy pieces. Keep scrolling to shop our specially curated edit of jorts to instantly elevate your wardrobe this summer and beyond. nordstrom.comBest Mid Rise JortsBP. Frayed Mid Rise Denim Jorts ($41, originally $55) While low-rise denim has been dominating the trend cycle in recent years, mid rise silhouettes are just as stylish and classic. From its slightly frayed hem to the subtle, relaxed waist, this BP. pair is a must.asos.comBest Dark-Wash JortsBershka Baggy Denim Jorts ($46) Hitting just a few inches below the knee, these baggy dark-wash shorts serve the ultimate Y2K vibes. They also come in a classic light wash. amazon.comBest Skinny JortsLevi's Women's Shaping Bermuda Shorts ($50) In case you're feeling inspired by Beyoncé in the early aughts or want a pair of jorts that will still show off your curves, this pick from Levi's is it. Made of high quality cotton and elastane and built with a tummy panel, these shorts give you the perfect stretch and look. Plus, there's no better place to buy your denim than from this household brand.urbanoutfitters.comBest Black JortsBDG Missouri Jort ($59) Calling all skate lovers! These black jorts from BDG features staple details like five-pocket styling and rigid cotton that softens with wear.shop.mango.comBest White JortsMango High-Waisted Denim Bermuda Shorts ($60) Nothing says summer like a white pair of shorts. A slightly shorter take on the fad, this high-waisted pair from Mango is ideal for any warm-weather outing, from a casual beach day to an impromptu road trip to the Hamptons for the Fourth of July. madewell.comBest JortsThe Essex Long Baggy Short ($88) Another trusted destination for denim? Madewell. This bestselling baggy number is made with the brand's premium cotton Cone® denim and sits perfectly at the mid-waist for that comfortable fit. Customers love it for its length and long-lasting comfort during wear. It also comes in two other washes: black and blue denim.freepeople.comBest Asymmetric JortsWe The Free Boomerang Long Shorts ($98) In case you're looking for a unique way to nail the trend, these Free People jorts are a great option. They feature an overlapping waistband and slightly pleated side-seam for the right blend of chic meets street.shop.diesel.comBest Designer JortsDiesel De-Sire Shorts ($120, originally $250) If you prefer a body-hugging jort with the right amount of stretch, consider this pair from Diesel. It features the trend's slouchy signature, but with a slightly slimmer leg. Plus, it's currently on sale for 52 percent off — you can't resist that.revolve.comBest Baggy JortsAGOLDE Baggy V Short ($188) Another sustainable pick, these AGOLDE shorts are made from 100 percent regenerative cotton. The subtle fading throughout also gives the perfect chic and grunge look. Naomi Parris is the assistant shopping editor at PS, based in New York. With over eight years of experience and previous roles held on the brand's Beauty and Operations teams, she enjoys telling stories that merge fashion, beauty, and Black culture. Naomi has also lent her skillful pen to Essence Girls United, Elle, Bustle, and Elite Daily. When she's not crafting shopping roundups, high-profile features, beauty op-eds, or trend guides, you can find Naomi behind her blog \"Eli-Nay,\" where she inspires readers through style guides, cultural pieces, and innovative content on her Instagram.",
